\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Now when were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 I was born in May, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname date}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname 
Year}{\xmlattrvalue 1897}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Day}{\xmlattrvalue 25}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Month}{\xmlattrvalue 5}}}May 25th, 1897{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 And whereabouts was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 It was in one of the suburbs of Bradford }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6441670\charrsid12130839 Low Moor,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839  near the station.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 What sort of a house was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Oh it was just a small through (?) with no bathroom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 How many bedrooms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 We'd only two bedrooms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 And what was the downstairs like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Downstairs, we'd only a very, a big kitchen, and a big, what we called "the Room". In Yorkshire we - well it was the sitting room, with a sitting room fireplace, which we used for special occasions, and Sundays, and so on, and we'd a kit
chen and just a sort of small, a small top of the cellar, a sort of cellar head where things were kept, and a fairly big cellar, two big cellars, a coal cellar and a keeping cellar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 What was there in the cellar then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Well there was a coal cellar
 and the washing materials were kept in the coal cellar, and large bread crocks, which were sometimes used for making home brewed beers, you know, dandelion and burdock, and that kind of thing. And we as young ones, my brother particularly, and my sister 
Dorothy, used to sneak down with a cup, and get a take a drink of these summer drinks that Mother made, before it was bottled.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Oh, I didn't know that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 What was the front room furniture like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Well, it wasn't like modern furniture,
 of course. We had a sideboard, and what we called the sofa, and a few easy chairs, a piano, and a bookcase, and perhaps one or two small tables.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 What sort of floor covering?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Well we, had, I will say that we had a good carpet. A Brussels carpet,
 I think my mother must have got it as a sale from a big house, because it was a particularly good carpet. And a nice rug, a nice black skin rug, we had. That is where we were for a time, but when we were, by the time I was a teenager (as well call them t
o
day) we moved to a house where there was more accommodation. By that time of course my eldest sister was married, and my two brothers had gone off to the war. The First World War. But we were very glad to have more convenience, and a good sized bathroom. 
In our little cottage home we had no bathroom, and I often wonder how eight of us managed to bath, but we did and we were very clean, we were kept very clean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 How did you heat the water?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6441670\charrsid12130839 Well we had a good side pan in the kitchen. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 My mother used on washing days and then of course we had a stove, and we had a big pan and kettle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 What was the stove like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 A gas stove, on which we could heat water.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 And an oven underneath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 No, this was just a separate ring. We had the old-fashion
ed range in the kitchen with a good oven, and this side pan which heated water, and in which my mother boiled her clothes on washing day. We managed very well indeed, with a large zinc bath, and we girls usually waited until a Saturday, a Saturday afterno
on. We had a bath once a week, at any rate, and the boys went to the baths. Went to the swimming baths, and they got showers regularly you see. So we managed fairly well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 How many brothers and sisters have you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Well I had three sisters, all older
 than myself, I was the youngest of six, and the two brothers. Three sisters and two brothers, so that we were six children. And we had to use the front room partly as sleeping accommodation sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 How was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Well because there were, we h
ad fairly big rooms, but the girls, at one time the boys also shared the parents bedroom, but on occasions we did have to use the sitting room. We managed very well.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Do you think that you were privileged in a way, being the youngest of a large family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Yes, I think probably I was. I was, I was spoilt to some extent, not by my parents, but my elder brother took an interest in me, and my eldest sister, but the one who loved me the most and took the greatest interest in me was the second one in the 
family. The one who, the only one who was not married. And she mothered me. And thought, she loved me and made a fuss of me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 What was your father's job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
My father was an engineer, connected with the railway. And I don't think it was his intentio
n at first because he had had a good education. I have a letter written by my father to my mother which I treasure, because it is in an educated hand. Good handwriting, good spelling, good English, and he really ought to have done something better. But, I
 
suppose by falling in love with my mother, and acquiring a family, when he was still young, he had to get a job to keep his family, having a sense of responsibility. But I think that if he had had opportunities that young people have today, he would have 
been something very different, because he was certainly a man with ability. And he had the education.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Was it a fairly well paid job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
No. They were, the jobs were not well paid in those days. They didn't find it easy. No, I don't know just what it was, but mind you, prices were low, the rents and rates in those days were very cheap, very low rated.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 The house was rented was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 I think that it was my mother's good management that really, was, we really ought to be thankful that
 she was capable of good household management, she seemed to manage the money very well indeed, and we were always well dressed. She was practical and made our clothes, I was once considered the best dressed girl in the village, sort of thing. She could c
ontrive -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 She made all your clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Yes. She, and then with the help of this sister, who took up sewing, she was the only one who didn't go to the secondary school, my sister Edie, and she helped, and by the time I was a teenager, I was a very w
ell dressed girl I was when I was at school. My mother contrived to make new clothes from old garments. Which a lot of people did in those days. But they weren't all as practical and as efficient as my mother. She was particularly good, at managing. How s
he fitted it all in I don't know because she did all her own baking you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Had she a strict household routine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
No, I don't think so. No, she was not that type of woman She was rather irregular with a lot of things, with her meals. No, but I th
ink that she fitted things in as best she could because my father's hours were not always regular you see and the children were at different schools with different hours and then she went, she went to an afternoon class at one time, I know, a sewing class
. But, we all seemed to come together for the evening meal and we all used to - read.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 It was your main meal was it, your evening meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Well when we were at school, locally of course, we, some of us were at home for the mid-day meal, but we all s
eemed to be in in the evening, for the evening meal. And we were all allowed to read at that meal, it was a sort of free and easy - and I think that's how we acquired the habit of reading. We were all readers. My Mother and Father included.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 What sort of books would you have in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Well, we'd the Bibles of course, and "Pilgrims Progress" and Dickens and Scott and the - some poetry books, I remember there was 'Sesame and Lilies' and I remember when my brother Victor went to the Grammar Schoo
l, at the age of ten, he was eight years older than I, he began reading of course, the more modern, and I can remember my mother throwing out one of Oscar Wilde was he? The man who was in trouble with the authorities over his irregular habits, sexual habi
ts of course, as we call them today, which were not considered - but I can remember she threw some of these books out, quite good books I suppose. I can't just remember all the books.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 How about newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Oh yes we had newspapers. We had the - I
 just forget whether we had a morning paper, I don't think morning papers were very popular then, it was mostly the evening paper we had. My parents were Liberals so we had the Liberal paper. The "Telegraph" was the Liberal paper and the }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197580\charrsid12130839 \lquote {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Argos{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}\rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839  was the To
ry paper. And the Church people usually took the "{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Arg}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197580\charrsid12130839 os}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 {\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
", the Tory paper, and the Methodists usually took the "Telegraph". And they were more of a liberal, more Liberal you see, all going to the Left, because the Labour movement was just starting and there
 was a move away from Liberalism to extreme, the extreme you see, towards the Labour Party. I don't know much about that thought, I don't know much about it,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12130839  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6441670\charrsid12130839 I was}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839  a child.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Were your parents interested in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Oh, very much so, yes. Most people, most Liberals had a photograph of 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Gladstone{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} hanging in their parlour. Oh yes, and probably a picture of Queen {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State
}}Victoria{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, they revered the old Queen you know, as she was called. Oh yes, yes. Yes. And they took an interest in politics, of course women didn't have a vote then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 But I suppose your father would vote?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Oh my father had a vote, yes. But women weren't supposed to take much interest you see. The Suffrage Movement came later, when I was, when I was preparing to go to college I think, I just forget the dates. But it was somewhere around the 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}First World{\*\xmlclose} war wasn't it? Just before, and during that period.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Had your parents any outside interests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Well my father was always a member of, what do you call those societies, -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6441670\charrsid12130839 Working Men's Club?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
No, he never did go to a Working Mans Club. The Oddfellows Society. I think that he was a member of the Oddfellows. There wasn't very much that people could be interested in. We attended a place of worship and we attended concerts, an
d they were both very fond of the theatre. My mother and father were very fond of the theatre. They used to take holidays together. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6441670\charrsid12130839 
And then they were fond of the theatre, good - the operas you know, and we were blessed in my city i.e. Bradford you see bec
ause we had, we had such people for the straight plays, we had Martin Harvey, I remember, who played "The Only Way" you know adapted from "The Tale of Two Cities" and we had Henry Ainsley, we had lots of Shakespeare companies, Ben Greet (?) and who were t
he others, I forget the name of them. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
I just forget. We were taken from school. And then of course we had the opera companies, I forget the names of them, and later, when I was a young teacher, we had the Beecham's Opera Company. Beecham tried to launch an 
Opera Company you know, and we all contributed but it came to nothing. I think that he was a spendthrift and he regretted that he hadn't been able to form this company. But we did admire him, Beecham was my favourite, what do you call them, conductor. And
 we went into the cheap seats - I'd forgotten, we used to go to the Saturday Evening Concerts, Friday night concerts, and Saturday night concerts, at St. George's Hall, we had the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City
}}Halle{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} concerts you know, regularly. And when we were old enough and could aff
ord, the seats in the, what we call the West Gallery, of St. George's Hall, we had to take our seats by ballot. They were the, not the cheapest seats, that was the centre gallery really, but it was a place of vantage, and marvellous for hearing. I remembe
r the first time I heard the Unfinished Symphony, I couldn't applaud.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 How old would you have been then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Oh, I might have been fifteen. I had heard good music before of course, but I remember -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Would your parents actually go with you or would you go -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
No, we went with our friends. They didn't always go, they couldn't always go. They went separately. I remember once my friend and I, we would be about sixteen, and my first opera was in the old Theatre Royal, on Manningham(?) Lane, and it 
was Faust, and I didn't know my mother and father were going, and we all attended the same one, and we all came home in the train together. But we happened to be with some young men friends, boy friends, and when they got into the same compartment on the 
t
rain, we were a bit disappointed, so we had to sit just prim and proper you know. But that was my first opera, and I think we stood in the back of the stalls, it was a small sort of homely theatre, we much regretted when it was closed. But I can remember 
the first opera, I can remember my first good concert, it was at St. George's Hall, hearing Fingel's Cave, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6441670\charrsid12130839 Mendelssohn\rquote s }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 "Fingel's Cave" and Schubert's Unfinished. I can remember those very well indeed. And how I could have just sat and hear}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6441670\charrsid12130839 d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839  them all over again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Was your father a handy man at all, did he do odd jobs in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Yes, yes, he did some odd jobs. He used to mend our shoes. Yes, he mended our shoes, because footwear, I think, was one of the, one of my mother's trials, we were rough 
on shoes. And although the boots, well I was very rough on footwear, I have a photograph of myself with a class, sitting in the front row, of one of the classes at the Infants School, and you have never seen children today with shoes like I am wearing, th
e
 toes were out! With climbing walls I suppose. And kicking stones! So that that was a big help. He cut the leather, and had a last and he soled and heeled out shoes and our footwear was examined periodically to see what was needed. And I remember those of
 
us that were particularly rough had to have, what did they call them? Protectors, in. Metal Protectors in the toes and heels, and round the edges, so that if we were rough, they had these metal protectors. We weren't, our footwear wasn't like it is today.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Did you see your father very much as children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Oh yes, we saw a lot of him and he used to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Did he play games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
I can't remember, that he played games. I can't remember that he played games. I think that our parents always ha
d too much to do to play games. That was the difficulty. I found that with my mother that she didn't give me, the time that I should have liked. She fed us, she clothed us, but I think they were so busy with that side of life, she saw that we had good rea
d
ing matter and we were encouraged to sew and knit. It was my mother who taught me to knit, I was very poor with my hands, but she taught me to knit, and to knit socks and stockings, and turn the heels, all that kind of thing, but I should never have learn
t at school. Because I know that I was very poor at that kind of thing. No, I don't think that they, they took us for walks. And we had holidays of course.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Where did you go on holiday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Well mostly of course to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10705778\charrsid12130839 
Ripon}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 . And that was heaven really. 
We stayed with an old aunt, my mother's aunt, who lived alone, she had been a widow. And we used to look forward to these holidays because it was real country and it was lovely. And I remember hot summer days, when there were humming bees in the hollyhock
s. Glorious long summer days and an occasional summer shower. Oh, it seemed to be much better weather than we have now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 About how long would you stay there, a week or a fortnight?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Oh sometimes we stayed quite a time if we had a month's holiday, I
 have been there a month. If there was no-one else. Because she had good accommodation for us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 How many of you would go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Oh two or three. Perhaps three sisters. I once went with my two brothers. They occupied one bedroom and I think I slept with
 Auntie, or she made me a little bed up in the spare bedroom, but I lived that holiday with two brothers because we went nutting and blackberrying, which we girls didn't usually do. We paddled in the river, and went with fishing nets you know, catching mi
nnows in the river near. Oh we loved }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10705778\charrsid12130839 Ripon}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 . We still do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Did you ever explore any further a field?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Oh yes, we used to wander to the villages round about, and then when I was in my teens, }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6441670\charrsid12130839 we}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839  had a long walk once with an older friend, who lived a few doors away, we went as far as Brimham Rocks}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6441670\charrsid12130839 ,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12130839  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
that is about ten miles away. We were good walkers you know. I think walking was our chief past-time, outside the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Had you bicycles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Ah now, you are asking me something. I never remember lea
rning to ride a bicycle. This is what happened, nobody could afford a bicycle. I didn't have one until I could afford to buy one of me own, till was turned twenty, till I earned my own money. No, there would probably be a boy in the neighbourhood with an 
o
ld bone shaker. No rubber tyres, just the bare framework, and we had a little run, a little hill, and several of us would play together on this bone shaker. We were pushed up and run down the hill. Sometimes an older one would run with us in case anything
 happened, but if we fell off, we fell off. But that's how I learned to ride, I must have been very small, I never remember learning how to ride a bicycle. But we didn't have them, I can't remember, our boys never had a bicycle. We had no toys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Had your brothers a bicycle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
No, our parents could not afford to buy a bicycle. And that is the truth. They couldn't afford anything like that. Although I suppose they were comparatively cheap.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Did your parents have a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Yes, they took holidays. But it was mostly, I think, visits to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10705778\charrsid12130839 Ripon}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
. And visits to relatives and friends not far away. My mother would go to visit relatives perhaps on the other side of the town. By tram, train and tram. Old friends you know and odd relatives, distant cousins.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Would your parents have people in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Oh yes, yes. That was our, one of the weekend enjoyment. Our house was open to our friends, our friends were always welcome. Mind you, my mother would always want to know who they were. We didn't have boyf
riends in much until we were older but then they were acquaintances, friends of the family in a way. But Sunday nights, after Chapel, we would all stream home, and we would have a sing song round the piano. Sometimes as many as twenty of us. Eventually we
 
played cards. At one time of course cards were thought to be wicked. But gradually I think our parents came to see that there wasn't much harm in cards. And I learned to play whist and simple card games when I was quite young. And enjoyed it. And of cours
e there was dominoes. Now my father played dominoes with the boys, with us sometimes. Dominoes and draughts. We always had dominoes and draughts. And later we had card games. But of course there was the piano you see.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8197580\charrsid12130839  Two of three,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839  my brother, two of my sis
ters played the piano, one in particular had special lessons and was able to accompany these sing songs at the weekend. And we all thoroughly enjoyed them. And that went on for years. I can remember as a small child you see, all these people coming in. I 
was sent off to bed when I was young, but later on when I was older I was allowed to stay up of course and join in the sing song.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Were your parents strict with you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 What sort of things did they mind about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Well, I think they set us a good e
xample. My mother always believed in example rather than precepts. And they set us a good example by, well by behaving nicely to each other. I think that is how we learnt. We were expected to be truthful and honest and obedient, it was expected of us. We 
were trusted. I think that we were brought up like that, that they trusted us to behave in a seemly manner always, wherever we were, and we trusted our parents to look after us I suppose. We }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6441670\charrsid12130839 
were}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839  very close together, parents and children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Were you punished at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Well I once had a good smack on the behind. But my dignity was hurt more than my flesh. And I can't remember what it was for, because I can remember my sister Edie, who mothered me a lot, always telling me what a good child I had been. I
 was not a forward unruly child, and I can't remember what I had done, it must have been something out of the ordinary. And of course children in those days were taught to be seen and not heard. And we were seen and not heard. We would never attempt to sp
e
ak when grown up people were speaking, we should keep in the background. We knew very well that if people came to the house to talk to my parents we would automatically disappear into another room, or go outside. Unless we were invited to stay. I think th
at, now that isn't how children do today. But I think that was the rule in most families. We were, at any rate, expected to behave like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Were they strict over your bedtimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Yes, very, yes. That was where the trouble }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8197580\charrsid12130839 lay. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 If one of us, well 
I had one sister particularly, who used to be, used to stay out later than was expected and she was always in trouble. Sister Dorothy. But she wasn't a bad girl. I can remember her getting into trouble. Yes, we were expected to go to bed. I remember when 
I
 was sixteen and a half, when my, the next sister to me was twenty-one and she was having a party, a mixed party, mostly from the Chapel, you know the Sunday School Chapel people, because that was sort of a social centre, as they are today, these places a
re today. And she had a mixed party when she was twenty-one. But I, being younger, was sent off to bed at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 9}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}
{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}nine o'clock{\*\xmlclose}.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Awful!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Yes, it was awful. I resented it, but I had to go, I think I remember sitting half way up the stairs, listening to the fun. It was mostly parlour games and music. And, they finished before eleven. Everybody would be out of the house by 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 10}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 30}}}half past ten{\*\xmlclose}
. Before eleven at any rate. Yes. Well we kept, we were always in bed I think before ten. Because parents retired you know, b
etween ten and eleven, at the latest. People didn't stay up then, there was nothing to stay up for. My mother would like an hour's reading, quietly by the fire, when we had gone to bed, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5586182\charrsid12130839 
I think they liked}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839  a nice quiet read. Perhaps talking over private affairs. And that is how we lived in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Were there any children who your parents wouldn't want you mixing with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Of course. There was one girl she said I mustn't associate with her again, because she told lies. My mother found her out in te
lling untruths, she said I mustn't go with her. Oh yes, my mother, she wasn't exactly a snob, but she was very particular with whom we associated. They had to be decent respectable people. Yes, she -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 What sort of an area was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Oh a working cl
ass area. We were all working class people. But very respectable people and respected by the community. When I went to Chapel win my father, he discontinued going, after a time, for some reason, but when he did go, he was a tall good looking man, and I us
e
d to be proud to walk up the road with him, to the Chapel. Because he always were morning dress, swallow tailed coat, grey striped trousers, swallow tailed coat and tall hat. And he looked the gentleman which he was. Although he was a working man, working
 men in those days were gentlemen. In every respect. Apart from a few who were of a different breed shall we say. But those with whom we associated were all respectable people and highly respected.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8197580\charrsid12130839  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 And I can remember, and my mother was the same. She was a v
ery good looking woman, they were a handsome couple, and when they had their silver wedding, it really was a lovely affair. Everybody, my mother was dressed beautifully, a special dress with a train, and I can remember it was chiefly family I think, oh we
 
had some friends, there were a few friends, my sister's friends, especially those who had any talents, vocal talents you see, or elocution, my brother had a friend who was an elocutionist, and my sister had a friend who was a marvellous singer, and a few 
l
ike that were invited. Quite a number probably because everybody paid so much, we had a new Chapel built, and of course it had to be paid for, and the money made at my parents Silver Wedding was the first large amount contributed towards paying off the de
bt! That was an interesting point.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 How old would you have been?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
I should be in my teens, I should be in my teens I should think. I may have been twelve or thirteen, I am going by the older ones you see, I can't quite remember. Just a minute. I can't just remember how old - should be, anyway I wasn't very old.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 The chapel obviously played an important part in your life, in a social way apart from anything else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Oh yes. Oh yes. We had the Annual Bazaar and during the week of course, when 
I was a child, there was the Band of Hope, every Wednesday evening, if you know what the Band of Hope was, ever heard of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Would you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
We did, we did. And I will tell you who led it as well. You have heard of Cedric Cliff, on the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5586182\charrsid12130839 Brains}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839  Trus
t, well his uncle, Mr. I forget his Christian name, Mr. Cliff. I didn't know until some years ago that our Mr. Cliff of the Band of Hope was Cedric Cliff's uncle. But }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5586182\charrsid12130839 evidentially}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839  it was so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 What would you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 At the Band of Hope? Oh we had demo
nstrations with alcohol, to show how it burnt! Oh yes, scientific demonstrations to show how dangerous alcohol was. And we sang songs of course. And we signed, I don't know whether we were asked to sign the pledge of course, of total }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5586182\charrsid12130839 abstinence,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839  and many of us did. Oh we were very sincere about it, we were very, it was a very important part of our lives, this Band of Hope.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 What sort of age group would go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Oh mostly the younger, the young people. But of course people were young then up to twenty-
five you see, up to, in their early twenties, from children, but it was mostly young people they used to try to get the young people, the Sunday School children. And we had this on a Wednesday evening. But of course there were, for the older ones, there w
ere prayer meetings. And Love feasts that I have heard my mother talk about. And then we had the Guild, the Methodist Guild, on a Friday night and those were very interesting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 What was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Well we would have a devotional, it was divided up into
 different, different groups, we'd have a devotional evening when the evening was devoted to devotional, you see we would have one social evening in the month, I just forget. But that was very interesting, the Guild. The Guild Meetings on a Friday night. 
And there would be special speakers you see. The Secretary would try to get some special speaker to come. And we would have a vocalist and of course hymns, and such like. So that really our whole life was c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5586182\charrsid12130839 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 ntred, in a way, round day schools and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5586182\charrsid12130839 the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839  place of worship. That was about all there was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 What were Sundays like?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Sundays? Well I often wonder, I think we used to, I wonder about children today, they seem to be in bed when we were in Sunday school because I remember, I think it started at nin
e, Sunday School was from nine to ten, or ten fifteen, and then the Chapel, we used to go through into the Chapel at ten thirty. And the Chapel service lasted from {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 
10}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 30}}}ten thirty{\*\xmlclose} until twelve, or {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 12}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}
{\xmlattrvalue 15}}}twelve fifteen{\*\xmlclose}. If he was long winded, the posh, if the preacher
 was what they called long winded and gave us a long sermon, if it was an interesting sermon it didn't matter how long it was, we enjoyed some sermons, if they were interesting but of course if they were boring we were bored. And glad to get out into the 
sunshine, if it was summer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 And then you went home and had dinner presumably?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Oh yes. The Sunday dinner was the special dinner. Roast beef and Yorkshire pudding. Two vegetables and perhaps an apple pie. Oh yes the Sunday dinner was looked forward
 to by everybody. Oh yes. And home made lemonade or home brew. Oh yes. And then afternoon Sunday school again you see. And evening Chapel. {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 18}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}Six o'clock{\*\xmlclose}. And then a sing song in the house, round the piano. After the evening service.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Would you all go and your parents go to the evening service?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
I think we all went. Unless we had some other engagement. Yes, I think we all went, unless we had some other engagement. Or unless my brothers perhaps had some homework they hadn't completed. That they had to 
have ready for Monday morning. And perhaps when we were young we were excused evening service. We weren't made to go but we took it for granted that we had to go, we never questioned it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Did you have meat every day? Would you have a joint of meat on Sundays and then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Oh we didn't have a joint of meat every day. Oh no. We would have a good joint of meat on a Sunday, and perhaps have it cold on Monday, if there was anything left, we used to like to come home from Chapel and cut some bread and mak
e a dripping sandwich with the cold meat, if we dare. But if there was anything left it was cold meat on Monday. But I think my mother had a routine with regard to food because she would probably do a good }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8197580\charrsid12130839 big}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839  meat and potato pie one day and fish another d
ay, probably fish on a Friday, and perhaps a good liver and Yorkshire pudding, liver and onions and Yorkshire pudding, one day, for winter that was a good meal. And potatoes baked in the skin you know, scrubbed and baked in the oven. We were well fed, but
 it was simple food. Not much fancy food. Good milk puddings and plain wholesome food.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 She baked her own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Yes. My father used to knead, if he could be at home. Because he was stronger. Yes, two stones of bread. I think Thursday was my mothe
r's baking day. Yes. And I used to love baking days. I didn't like washing days, I always hated everything to do with washing, except clean clothes! But baking days it was, really it was the whole day. White bread, brown bread, 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Yorkshire{\*\xmlclose} tea cakes, pies, s
ponge cakes, everything. And at the end of the day of course it was piled up on the kitchen dresser, with a cloth over, and probably it lasted the week. Not a lot of fancy cakes. In season there would be fruit pies, but we didn't have a lot of fancy cake 
during the week!
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Had you shops near by?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Yes, not very far away. Yes, within easy walking distance.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 What would your mother buy most things there then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 She was a member of the Co-operative Society. Which was really at first I suppose fo
rmed for the benefit of ordinary working people so that they could buy their goods, good goods, good quality goods, at wholesale price. I find it has never worked out like that. It was called the Wholesale Co-operative Society but the prices of recent yea
r
s have really been above those in the other shops. But it was good stuff, and of course there was a dividend, and the dividend in those days was quite good. I have known it be as much as half a crown in the pound! So that it was a consideration, a woman c
o
uld save quite a good sum if she saved her bonus. At the Co-op as it was called. But my mother never ran up bills you know. Everything was paid for. I don't know whether some people did, but she didn't. No, she used to budget and she knew how much she cou
ld spend. And that was it. And it was paid for.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 I suppose if bigger things were needed she bought them in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Bradford{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
I don't know. She probably bought some things in the City. Fruit perhaps. The perishable fruit. Yes, my mother used to go on a Saturday, especially Saturday evening, because then strawberries in season }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8197580\charrsid12130839 were}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839  sold cheap on a Saturday. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197580\charrsid12130839 Any}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839  of the soft fruit you see, they fruit merchants would lot a basket of strawberries, or a basket of raspberries, or any of the currants, go more cheap
ly on a Saturday evening, rather than keep them to perish over the weekend. So that my mother had an eye to that. And she'd prepare the fruit and get busy, probably on the Monday, and with jam. Jamming. Which was, of course that was a big saving. She alwa
ys had a big stock of preserves. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5586182\charrsid12130839 Strawberries and raspberries and blackcurrants and oh marmalade in season. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Yes, they did all that kind of thing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Had you any garden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 No, not much garden. No, very little garden. No. We should all have liked a gar
den, but we didn't have much. I used to go to play with a friend who had a big garden, and I enjoyed that very much. We had parks of course to play in. And I think it was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5586182\charrsid12130839 safe}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839  in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 You had open fields then didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Yes, it was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5586182\charrsid12130839 safe}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839  
then for children to play. And to wander off too to some extent. There was the danger of course of water. We couldn't all swim. But there was no danger of awkward people. A child being confronted with awkward people. Only now and again, }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5586182\charrsid12130839 there was}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839  some quee
r person. But we had plenty of places to play in. Unless of course the farmer was strict, we were trespassing and causing damage on his property.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Had you cats and dogs at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 We didn't have a dog, I can't remember that we had a cat. But a lot o
f people had a cat, but not a lot of people had a dog. No, I can't remember many people having a dog. It was very unusual. I think it was childless people. There were people who had dogs, I remember, because the people who lived next door to us, they were
 childless and they had a dog, a big collie dog. But not many people had dogs.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Had you any pets at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Yes, we had a rabbit. We once brought home two rabbits from }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10705778\charrsid12130839 Ripon}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 , the old man next door bred rabbits, and I had always begged for a rabbit, 
I loved rabbits, children do, they are soft and silky, and we brought home two. One a black and white one and one a grey Dutch rabbit. The morning after the black and white one was dead. But the grey Dutch rabbit lived about nine years on its own. It was 
a
 real pet. Yes. It was a real pet. And then my brother, of course, he had pets of a kind. He was a schoolboy naturalist and he brought home anything that was alive, anything. Beetles, frogs, he once brought home a grass snake, which was harmless of course
. Guinea pigs and tame mice and that kind, he would make a cage for them you know as boys will. I can remember guinea pigs and mice. But the rabbit, I think was my pet, I loved to hold it in me arms, I think we called it Silky.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Would you help your mother much in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Help?! Why of course!!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 What sort of jobs did you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Oh we did everything. I took no part in any washing at all. But I helped with the baking from a very early age. And that was how I learnt to make bread. Although I 
turned out to be a school teacher, I learnt to make bread when I was quite young. First she would let me grease the tins and put them to warm, she would let me get the water, to make the dough, and I had to get it the exact temperature, you know, and then
 
I was allowed to put the salt round the edge, I was allowed to take out the leaves from the oven and knock them to see if they were ready, they were baked. And when at last I was allowed to knead the dough, and shape loaves, I mustn't have been very old b
ut I have always been able to make bread. I can't remember when I learnt to make bread. We all learnt to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197580\charrsid12130839 bake}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
 and cook. And some of us were better than - my eldest sister wasn't very good. She was more booky, but the sister next to me, she was very good at 
baking and cooking. And of course we helped with the cleaning. And the other three sisters older than myself did all the ironing. So that my mother had quite a lot of help.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 What did she do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 My mother? She }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197580\charrsid12130839 did}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839  the washing. And she did a lot of s
ewing. She had quite enough to do. She was kept very busy mending. We didn't wear new clothes every day you know. Our things were patched and darned. All our clothes were patched and darned. I think that she would spend a whole day, after washing day, dar
ning socks for a start, and sewing buttons on. We never had buttons off. Our clothes were always neat, no I think my mother, she never had an idle minute.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 How about your brothers. Would they help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Oh, they would clean the windows on a Saturday mo
rning. Perhaps swill the back yard. My eldest brother used to dust sometimes. \{ILLEGIBLE\}
 They didn't do a great deal - oh and then they cleaned the shoes. They sometimes cleaned everybody's shoes, the boys did. I don't think they did, they didn't do bed m
aking and laying the table, anything like that, it was left to the girls, you know the domestic side of the - house.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 How many beds were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Well we used to share beds in those days, two together you see. So that's how we slept, four beds for
 eight people. I suppose, there was a cradle, an old cradle, that was kept upstairs. I can remember that. An old fashioned cradle, I don't know where it eventually went to, but all the babies, when they were babies, must have been rocked in the cradle. Cr
adles have gone out haven't they. I don't know -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 You said you lived in your house on Railway Terrace, until you were - about how old were you when you moved?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 I think I would be between - about 16.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 And why did the family move at this point?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Why did they move? Well we hadn't much convenience in the old, smaller house, and I think as grown-up children we felt we ought to have something with more convenience, a bathroom for example, and more rooms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Was there more money coming in at this stage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Oh yes, you see I was the youngest and well the war years, that was during the war years you see, and I am not sure who was married, my eldest sister was married, I'm not sure whether the boys were married and I'm not sure if Dorothy, the o
ne next to me, older, was married. But they did contribute to the household expenses, and improved conditions generally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 So in fact you stayed so long at the first house because of the money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Yes, I think so, yes I think that probably, it was no
t easy because apart from the second sister, next to the eldest, there were six of us, we were all sent to the Higher Grade School, and two were qualified teachers, the boys were, the younger son was in a good position, that, you know, had prospects, and 
I
 was the youngest and I was due to go to College, for training to be a teacher, and of course it hadn't been easy for a mother, managed on one wage. And in those days schooling was expensive, although I had a free scholarship, but the older ones, I think 
there was some payment.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 So in fact your parents' standard of living stayed fairly low because they were educating -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 The standard of living my dear was not low, we were always -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Well, as far as housing went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 As far as housing went, but
 other conditions, the food was always substantial and good, and we were clothed as, we were called 'better' children because my mother was very competent and I was considered one of the best dressed children, the photographs in fact show that. No finery,
 but good, good clothes. And my father did the shoe repairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Did your mother always }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5586182\charrsid12130839 made}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839  the family clothes or would she buy any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 There was very little bought.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 What about your father's clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Well of course she had to - she made the b}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8197580\charrsid12130839 oy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197580\charrsid12130839 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
 things, she went to classes and improved her skill with the needle and the sewing machine, and did quite a lot, and then improvised from older clothes, my father's things were bought, I suppose, I don't remember her making his things, but she made mo
st of our things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Have you any idea how old your father was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Yes, my parents were both 32 when I was born and I was the last child.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 And had your father always had the same job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 No, no. I don't know much about it, b
ut what I do know, I've gathered that as a young man he was apprenticed, he was well educated and he was apprenticed to one of the best firms in Bradford, Christopher }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5586182\charrsid12130839 Pratt\rquote s}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 , the carpet specialists, very high class, furnishings, and I think if he'd remain
ed there he would have risen to a good position because according to letters that I have his handwriting, his English, his standard of education was fairly high, he'd been to a special school you see, and he was worthy of really a very good job, but, I su
ppose when he fell in love with my mother and they were married, apprenticeship didn't bring in much money and he had to seek for something that would, some job whereby he could support a wife and a coming family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 So he started on the railway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 He started on the railway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 And he stayed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
He stayed there until he retired. We were all rather sorry because we knew that he could have done much better.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Did he ever do any casual work or outside jobs at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 No. No. I can't remember him doing any casual work. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Was he ever out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Not while I was, not in my remembrance. I think he had on a period but I can't remember anything about it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Had your mother worked before her marriage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Yes, but she was only a girl
 and she suffered from ill health. She had a period in hospital with I suppose it was called consumption, I think at some time or other, we did learn that she, she was dismissed from hospital, (you don't call it dismissed to you?) With only one lung, she 
had had a period of tuberculosis, from which disease, a number of her relatives, sisters and brothers, and her mother died. Bovine tuberculosis, because they were farmers you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 So had she ever left home and worked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Left home? Well she'd no par
ents, my mother, my mother was left an orphan at the age of 11. And that is partly why she was married early, because she was brought up partly, I think as a child, by grandparents, and then by good people. I don't know how she came in contact, I think pr
obably it was through }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5586182\charrsid12130839 Kickgate (?)}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839  Chapel in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Bradford{\*\xmlclose}
, because Mrs. Lingard, Lingards owned a big store in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Bradford{\*\xmlclose}
, it was burnt down during the last war, but she learnt a lot, and she learnt a lot of good housekeeping from her friends, her friend's mother
, Mrs. Pickles, and from Mrs. Lingard. She learnt the laundry, cookery and all the rest of it, so that she was quite a competent young housewife.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Would she have a set household routine? Would she always do the rooms out on a certain day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 In my t
ime, that I remember, I never remember my mother doing any rooms out, we girls did everything. No, I don't remember my mother doing much. Apart from her cookery and sewing, when we were old enough to help, we did the bedrooms, I can remember I did them, w
e all helped. We took it for granted that it was, well we just did it, we were just taught how to do things, and how not to miss the corners.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Did your father help your mother at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Oh a lot, he did, he was a good husband and a good father. In 
fact, I've seen him knead two stones of flour into dough because it was home baked bread in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Would he help with things like making fires and bringing in the coals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Oh yes, in fact he helped with everything as he could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Would he help her with you at all when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Yes, yes, I remember he helped to look after us, I remember him, I think he used to bath some of us, when we were children. Generally take an equal share in the caring for the children, I being the younges
t of course can't remember what happened before I was born, you know I can't remember what happened to the elder ones. Oh yes, he helped a lot in the house and with the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Did he read stories to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Yes, and he took us, until he left the
 place of worship he used to go to the services at the Chapel, we were Wesleyan Methodists, and I was proud to walk with my father because he was tall and good looking, and I think I told you before, that he dressed on Sundays in grey striped trousers and
 tail coat and a tall silk hat and wore gloves, he was gentlemanly in appearance and in manners.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 When you were small did the older ones help the younger ones with eating or getting dressed or?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Yes, yes, the older ones helped, the two elder siste
rs, the eldest and the next, the second one, particularly, in fact mothered me. She loved me, and she cared for me, and one thing she did love to do and that was to attend to my golden hair. Brush it and comb it and attend to my hair, wash it I suppose as
 well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 When you were a school child did you have to go to bed at a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Oh we all had a certain time, we were expected to be in bed, I think the whole household was quiet, round about ten. Even the older children, the house was quiet by 
ten, I think it was about eight, when my sister, four and a half years older than I, had her twenty-first birthday party. Did I tell you this before? }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5586182\charrsid12130839 
Yes, I was sent to bed at the age of 16 and a half at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 9}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}nine o'clock{\*\xmlclose}.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 What about when you were small, when you were starting school say, six and seven, what sort of time would you go to bed then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 I shouldn't think it was much after seven or half past.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 And who was it that put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Usually, this sister I loved, the second sister, ten years older than myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 And what age would you be when you put yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Oh I can't just remember, I suppose gradually as the years went on, oh I should think by the time I was nine I should be going off to bed on my own, getting washed and ready for morning.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
When you lived on Railway Terrace you said there would be girls had one bedroom and you shared a double bed in one bedroom, what happened when you moved to the other house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Well by that time of course the boys had been ser
ving in the Forces, my eldest sister was married, so that there were really only three girls in the house and he had more accommodation. I just forget whether, we shared the two rooms, the two extra rooms you see, with three good bedrooms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 So were you still sharing a bed then or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
I think I had the little bedroom and I had a bed to myself by then. The smaller, you know, one was rather smaller than the other. We did share beds occasionally, especially if we had someone to stay or there was someone home, one of the boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 When you were still on Railway Terrace which room would you have a bath in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Oh the kitchen always, the warm kitchen. It was always cosy and warm. The doors were locked of course, Saturday afternoon, the two doors were locked, the curtains drawn. It was quite comfortable and pleasant.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 And would you always have your clean clothes on then or would you wait until Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Oh I think we should change into clean clothes straight away. We always had a set of clean clothes ready, aired and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Did your family always have their meals in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Oh occasionally we used the sitting room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 What sort of occasions would those be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Oh weekends and parties and er - we had a sit round the fire perhaps an
d a small table you see, little something similar to today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 And would you have breakfast actually as a family or was it more in shifts, when you were at school I am thinking of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Well all those who were going out for nine o'clock, I think we prob
ably four or five or us at any rate, I think by that time the eldest sister was married and we should probably, all the children would sit round together. I can't remember my mother getting up and looking after us, we used to get our own breakfasts. We di
d. I don't think my mother got up to look after us, we gradually became independent. Looked after ourselves. The older ones looking after the younger ones and with it being a small house, the fewer people in the kitchen the better.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 What would you have for your breakfasts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Ah. Porridge. Coffee usually, not much tea, because the boys were, the elder brother particularly was fond of coffee and we had a mill, a coffee mill and ground our own coffee. And certain times of the year we used to go mushroom
ing, and we'd have cooked mushrooms, mushroom soup for breakfast. Yes, we'd have bacon and egg, porridge, we didn't have these cer}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5586182\charrsid12130839 eals}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839  they have today, and my mother used to make frumenty.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 What's that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 It's made with pure wheat. I couldn't tell
 you just how to make it, but my mother was a firm believer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 So, when you moved you had a larger patch of land you said?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Yes, till my parents decided that they'd have some poultry, and these hens provided us with eggs, very acceptable.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Did you}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5586182\charrsid12130839  pickle eggs}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Yes, always. For winter. Yes, when there was a shortage.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Did you grow fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Just small bits of lettuce and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Who was it that did the gardening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Oh anybody, anyone. We all had a, mother and elder brother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Was either your father's or your mother's food ever different from the children's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 No, I don't think so. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Would your father have more meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 My father was a Vegetarian. Yes, he didn't eat meat. Cheese and veg
etables and a lot of green stuff, but not meat, my mother loved meat.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Did you ever say grace at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Yes. At the weekends when we were all together, but I don't think during the week because we didn't always take our meals all together. Usually the evening meal I think we had altogether. When we were allowed to read. We all read.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Would your parents let you talk during meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Yes, but I think we were more interested in reading than talking, but we were allowed to talk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Did your mother expect you to always eat all that she gave you or were you allowed to pick out what you wanted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Oh I think we were expected to eat what was provided. There was no wastage.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 So would she make you eat up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Yes. Much to our annoyance and disgust and displeasure.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Did your stay at the table until you had finished then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 I think when we were young yes, usually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Did you have to ask when you wanted to get down from the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Yes, usually. Until we were older.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 And did you have to wait until all the family had finished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 I think so, yes, I think so yes, usually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 And could you ever ask for second helpings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Oh yes, it doesn't mean that we always got them!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Well yes, we were taught to eat correctly, to use, yes. My father was very particular about that. I can remember my father tapping my sister Dorothy, if she didn't follow table etiquette correctly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 When all of you were at a meal, did you all have your own places at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Yes, I think we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 And would your mother always serve out the food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Yes, I think it was mother who usually served the food.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 And would she serve the youngest first or your father first or?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Oh I can't quite remember but I think it was mostly Father I can't just remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Would you say your mother was an easy person to get on with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
When we were young yes, but when we reached what is now called teenage and we became interested in the opposite sex you see, then she showed her possessiveness and she was not so easy.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 And what was your father's attitude?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 I think he left it mostly to Mother, she was the stronger personality.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Was she affectionate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Not demon
strative in affection. I don't think we ever saw much demonstration of affection, as I have seen since I left home, in fact I would have liked more affection shown That's why I clung to the sister who showed me it, I once asked my mother if she was my rea
l mother because she was so busy that I think she left me quite a lot to the care of this older sister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 So if you had any worries as a child would you share them with her or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 I can't remember ever sharing them with my mother, I think we mostl
y kept them to ourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Did your parents bring you up to behave to your brothers and sisters in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Oh they were expected to behave nicely to each other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 And what if you hit one of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 I don't think we did much hitting, not in, not while she was present.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Do you think that they had certain hopes about their children that they had a certain idea of what sort of people they wanted you to grow up to be?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Oh definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 What sort of ideas did they have on this do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Well they wanted us to attain good positions in life, to be good in conduct and to grow up to be useful citizens.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 So did they bring you up to think of certain things as being most important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Oh I think general behavi
our was very important, and to work industriously. And to do our best in every way, whatever we did, to do it with a zest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 What were their views about swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Oh we never heard anything like that? We never heard any bad language at all, we hea
rd it in the streets of course, and some of the words we heard we, well I didn't understand, not until I was much older. It was there that oh no we never had any bad language of any kind from our parents or from each other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Were you ever punished at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Oh yes, when it was necessary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 By whom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Usually Mother, I can't remember Father taking part. But we didn't need much punishment because I think we adhered strictly to the expected rules of behaviour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 What sort of things would they punish you for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Oh, direct disobedience. I think that's all.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Would you say you got your ideas about how to behave from one parent more than the other, or was it equally from them both?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Oh I think probably Mother was the stronger characte
r and she instilled into us the rules of behaviour, honesty, obedience, and all the rest. According to the Bible teachings I should think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 I would like to ask you about what sort of things you would do when you met actually as a family. What would you
 spend your evenings, if you were all in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Oh we were doing homework weren't we, most of the time. Because we all had homework to do. Sewing, knitting, music.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 What would your parents be doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Well, we all did, we were all, all the family, 
fond of reading. Parents as well as children, so that we all indulged in reading and enjoyed it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Were birthdays anything special?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Yes, to some extent. Nothing very big like they are today but they were recognised and we had a sort of little fete day. Or something special at the weekend. Presents.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Would you have any visitors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Well when we were small we might have a few little friends, but I think apart from my sister's 21st birthday, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 What was Christmas Day like?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Oh now C
hristmas was a good day. Yes. Christmas had the magic that has since been lost. It was a really lovely time Christmas was with friends and carol singing, parties, new clothes, party dresses and all the rest of it, good food. But it didn't arrive until Chr
istmas Eve, there was nothing, we had lovely surprises you see, because it wasn't like it is today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 And you said your parents were very fond of reading, would they ever read out loud?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 No, I don't think so, no I think we all indulged in our reading quietly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Did you ever have any family prayers at all, apart from saying grace?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 No, nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Were you ever taken out visiting neighbours, relatives, friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Yes, I was, I don't know what happened before my time but I was t
aken to friends by my mother and sometimes by this special sister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 And were you ever taken out shopping at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Where to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
We went into town. We were about three miles from the nearest city, we were taken shopping for new shoes and that kind of thing you see, and material for clothes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Did you ever go out with just your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Maybe just occasionally, I can't remember. I being the youngest you see, was taken out mostly by the elder ones. My eldest sister and her }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197580\charrsid12130839 fianc\'e9}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839  would take me with them and the special sister always took me with her, she was very fond of me, and my elder brother, but the younger brother and the sister next to older, no. I was the kid. And I wasn't wanted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Did you ever have any other outings with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Well I had, I was taken to the seaside, and of course I was taken to my mother's birthplace with them, when I was quite young, until I was old enough to go either with one of the others or on my own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 When you were still a schoolchild, what would you spend your Saturdays doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
I think it was mostly outings in the summer, and in the city there were Saturday evening concerts, popular concerts at the Methodist Central Hall, good concerts, and we used to attend them. When we were in our teens, and the 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Halle{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} concerts and the permanent orchestra concerts at St. George's Hall.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Had you any Sunday School outings at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 I can't remember that we had any Sunday school outings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 What was your }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197580\charrsid12130839 parent\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839  attitude over playing games on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Well I think they had a strong objection. Sunday was Sunday. No, we just read or we had music round the piano, but I don't think we indulged in any games, if we did we did it on the sly.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Was your Father interested in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Yes, very much so. We were, well my parents were both Liberals, but as the new idea of Socialism crept into politics he changed and he became a follower of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197580\charrsid12130839 Batchford}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839  and the other Socialist leaders.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Have you any idea what party he voted for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
He voted for the Liberals up to, in the early part we were definitely Liberals, and brought up to belong to the Liberal party.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Did he vote Socialist at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Later? My father changed to Socialism.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Before 1918 would this be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Well
 I think so, yes I think so. Because I remember you see before 1918 I was 21, so I think it would be before that time, oh it would be, definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Was he a member of the Party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 I think he was. I think he was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Was he a member of the Labour Party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Of the Labour Party.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Did he ever work for the Party at all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 I don't think so. He hadn't much time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Would he attend any meetings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 I think he would attend meetings. But he didn't take any official positions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Was your mother interested in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
They were interested in politics, but my mother remained a Liberal all her life, she didn't change.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Have you any idea why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 I think it was just her views. She didn't like the extreme, certainly she didn't belon
g to the Tory group, and she didn't like the extremists in the Labour group.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 What were your parents other interests, what would they spend their spare time doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 I think they hadn't much spare time for one thing and their chief interests were u
s, the children. And our careers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 You said your mother attended a sewing class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Well when I was a small child she'd taken it, I'd go to the afternoon class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Was your father ever a member of any }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197580\charrsid12130839 evening class}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 He was a member of the, w
hat do you call it? What do you call those? The Oddfellows. But I don't think he was a member of anything else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Would he spend most evenings at home?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Would your mother ever manage to get out and enjoy herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Only to visit friends and to go to concerts.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Was your father interested in any sport at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Well yes I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 What sort of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Well I think it was cricket chiefly. Cricket was cricket then in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Would he watch or would he play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 No, I don't remember my father playing, but he'd watch a cricket match.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 And were your parents ever members of any saving clubs at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 I don't think so, I can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 When you were a child, who did you play with most, with your brothers and sisters or neighbours' children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Neighbours' children. There were neighbours' children I played with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Whereabouts would you play, the garden, the street, the yard, or what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Well we had, not far away there was a field, we used to l
ove to play in, make a swing on the trees. We were surrounded by green fields, and during the summer we played there. In the winter of course it was mostly indoors.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 And you would play in the other children's home then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Not much, it was mostly in my own home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 What sort of games did you play as children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Dominoes, draughts, snakes and ladders, some card games, when cards were allowed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 How about outdoor games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Oh yes, outdoor games. We didn't play tennis until I was nearly gro
wn up, because we didn't play at school. It was mostly walking I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Would your parents mind who you played with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Definitely, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Why do you think this was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Well there were certain families who hadn't our standards of behaviour an
d of course my mother was always suspicious that we might be contaminated I suppose by girls and boys who had lower standards, say of morality. Because we've always had that type of person, haven't we?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Did you have any spending money as children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
We had a little spending money but it was only a small piece of money, a halfpenny or a penny, when we were small.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 What would you spend it on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Sweets, mostly. Only once a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Would your mother ever get any help in looking after her house or family from any relatives, friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
I don't think so, not much. Unless a relative came to stay. Or she was not well and a neighbour came in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Had your parents any relatives living near?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 My father had a mother and a sister, that was my grandma and auntie.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Where did they live?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Well there were, they lived a distance away until my parents found a house nearer because of their ill health, they needed to be looked after to some extent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 So would your parents see them fairly frequently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Yes. But those were the only relatives. The old aunt that used to live at Ripon of course, that was a distance away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Had your parents any friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 And when would they see them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Well during the sum
mer of course, when it was pleasant to get out visiting. And Christmastime. I think any time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Were these your mother's friends, your father's friends, or friends of them both?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Partly, friends of them both.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Had your mother any friends of her own that she'd go and see by herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Perhaps other women she met at the place of worship. I don't think, I think most of the friends were joint friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Would you invite your friends in, or would your parents ever invite their friends in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Yes, both. We visited each other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 For a meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Yes, probably, for tea. Not usually for anything but tea, or an evening meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 And would your parents' friends just call in or was it always invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Oh it may have been both, sometimes invitation, sometimes just call in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 What would your parents do when they went and visited their friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Oh it was mostly chatting I think, about their affairs, their children and so on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Not making their own amusements?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 It would b
e just, I suppose, chatting, gossip. Or perhaps looking at the gardens or something like that, if they had a garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Many people split up pre-1918 society into distinct social groups, would you say that it was a valid thing in your experience of the w
orld before 1918 that you could divide people up into broad strata?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Do you mean class? Oh I think so. Oh yes we were always very, those who doffed their caps to those a little bit above, and those who were ready to accept the nodding and doffing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 What class would you say your family belonged to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Well at first we were the working class, definitely working class people, we couldn't be any other. But we had friends who were a little bit higher than ourselves and we had relatives who were in a class higher. My father had cousins.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 What sort of people were on the same sort of level as you though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Well most of the people who attended the same place of worship.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Would you say that Chapel people were different from Church people then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Yes, definitely they were. The Chapel people were mostly Liberal and the Church people were mostly Conservative, or Tory as we called them. Definitely so. And the Chapel people usually took the Liberal newspaper, evening newspaper and the Church peop
le usually took the Tory paper.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 And which ones were the better off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 I don't think there was much difference in them, in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10705778\charrsid12130839 their state,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839  at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Were your brought up to treat people of one sort differently to people of another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 We were n
ot. But there was a distinct difference. We didn't seem to mix as much with the Church group as we did with our own group. And as children, when the voting time came round, there was definite enmity between us. Yes. Oh yes. I forget the songs we used to s
ing, but we children didn't understand much about it, but we knew that we were rivals. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Was there anybody you would call Sir or Madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
No, I can't remember that we ever did call anybody Sir or Madam, No. No. We were on a friendly footing with relatives and friends and we would call them by their names, if we were in conversation with them. Mrs. or Mr. so and so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 In your area who were thought of as being the most important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 In what way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Well in social standing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Well
 I think it was a question of money again. Those who had plenty of money and opened bazaars and gave gifts of money to this that and the other, I think they were looked up to. But those of us who knew them, could see through some of their }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197580\charrsid12130839 hypocrisy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 . You know what I mean by.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 What sort of people were these? Were these the farmers or employers or shopkeepers or what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
I think they were probably heads of departments in some of the works. On the railway. Those in the higher positions on the railway and in works.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Where you lived, would you say that all the people in the working class had the same standard of living?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Well where we lived there were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10705778\charrsid12130839 twenty eight hou}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 ses and just recently an old neighbour of ours, who lived next door, we were reckoning up and I think it was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10705778\charrsid12130839 fifteen, sixteen or seventeen}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839  neighbours' children went in for teaching, out of those }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10705778\charrsid12130839 
twenty eight }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 houses. And some of the people in them, only small houses, except the very, at each end, and they were considered dear houses, bu
t they were considered well really a better class, although they were working class, they were somehow of a higher group. They were mixed, but there were certain families, certainly with higher standards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Was there a distinction between craftsman and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
No, it wasn't anything to do with jobs, it was to do with the character of the people. My Mother and Father, working class, and there were others of the same, but they had ambitions to be educated. Now there were others who would spend the
ir leisure time in the public house and we had nothing to do with them. My parents would sit by the fireside reading, when they'd be spending their time at a club or a pub. That was the distinction, nothing to do with where you worked. You could be a work
ing man and yet a gentleman, in those days. And there were a lot like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Do you think your mother ever saw herself as belonging to a certain social -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Oh no, I don't think she was ambitious, she wasn't a - she wanted us to be better off in every way than she had been, because she had no chances, but she'd no room for the other type of person who were perhaps snobbish, snobbish type of people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Do you think it was possible to move from one social class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Oh they did, gradually, didn't we, through the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 I mean in the period before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Well I don't think it was as easy then, I don't think it was as easy to move, not for the parents, the children gradually rose to a higher class group, but I think, I think people then p
ut more importance on character than they did on class position. That's what I feel about it. You judged a person more by the character than by the class position.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Was your house always a rented one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Yes. Always. Until I was grown up when my par
ents bought a pleasant smaller house just suitable for them in a pleasant place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Did you ever see your landlord at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Yes, when he called for rent.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 What sort of landlords were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Well when we lived in the small house [i.e., Rail
way Terrace], I think so much was deducted from my father's wages to pay for the rent. Later the landlord was quite a decent sort of person, with regard to repairs and all that kind of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Do you think that the police at that time would treat different sorts of people in different ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Well I couldn't say, I can't remember having much contact with police.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 School. How old were you when you first started school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 I think I should be about three. Three and a bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Was it morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 All day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 What sort of school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 A church school. They were mostly church schools.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Was it a mixed school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Yes, the infants.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 And how far away was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Not far, a few minutes walk from where we lived.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 And who did you go with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Can't remember going with anyone? Can't remember. I suppose a few of us went together, because my sister, by the time I went to the Infants School, she would already be in what we now call the Junior, wouldn't she?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 So would you have your mid-day meal at home then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Yes, always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 What did you think about school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Well sometimes I liked it and sometimes I didn't like it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 What were your teachers like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Well they varied, some were kind and understanding and othe
rs were not. I can't remember much about the Infants School except occasion all, just little odd things, but I remember the next school, for the Juniors from - what was it? - 7 to 14 then, just a Girls' School, another church school but not mixed. The hea
dmistress didn't want it mixed and she seemed to choose her scholars, but she was a martinet. Kindly at heart, but she was severe and strict. There were one or two other teachers who were not so strict, more kindly and understanding, but she was a terror.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 What sort of things would she stress as being important. Was she especially interested in punctuality or? ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
She was very, she was, everything was important not just one thing. Punctuality, deportment, behaviour, work, no slackness. We were taught to work and to work hard, and to behave properly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Were you ever punished at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Punished? We were! I had the stick for mis-spelling two words and I can remember what they were? Necessary and Elizabeth. But it was ridiculous giving a chil
d the stick, it wasn't a cane it was a stick, a pointer, a wooden pointer, and I saw this headmistress once, because a girl was slouching and lazy, at least she was said to be so, she was run round the long schoolroom, run, with the headmistress holding a
t the back of her neck "Waken up, waken up, waken up girl"!! And yet, when she retired, she was very kindly she was always pleased to meet us. I can remember, I still have cards that she sent me. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Were the children at that school from the same sort of homes as your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Yes. Some a bit better off financially and others probably not so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 You stayed there until you were 14 did you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
No, I left with getting a free scholarship to what was then called the secondary school, at all. I was four years at the junior school, then a few of us sat for the special examination, it was called the scholarship examination in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 And was the secondary school very different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Well of course it was different. It was bigger for one th
ing. It wasn't a good building. Not as they are today. The headmistress and the staff shared one room, only a small room. And the main schoolroom was used, it was not, the premises were not good, and then we had several rooms scattered, part of an old hou
s
e. Then there was the cookery room that was part of a Sunday school, five minutes walk away. The gymnasium was a distance away. The science lab. Was what we called the "tin tabernacle" it had two classrooms and laboratories with a galvanised iron roof. Th
at was separate from the main building.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 What were the teachers like there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Oh they were the same, some we loved and some we disliked very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 And were the children there from widely differing sorts of backgrounds?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Oh they were yes. 
We'd some very well to do girls, and on the other hand some very poor girls, from poor homes. Very widely different.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Did your parents show any interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 They did! They showed interest all the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Would they ask you what you were doing at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Oh yes. And they of course we had reports.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 They wouldn't ever go and see your teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Oh I can't remember. Perhaps just now and again when it was necessary to talk over things. But not much. There was not much contact.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Had you any sort of uniform at your secondary school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Except for games and gymnasium as we called it, that was a gymslip and a white blouse, but normally, doing apart from that, we wore just ordinary clothes, as you can see from the photographs.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 White long sleeved blouses and?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
A gymslip, a pleated gymslip, and a tie. Colours were green and red I think. Green and scarlet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 And everybody wore this did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 We didn't wear them for lessons. Only, we changed for gym and for games, hockey.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 You stayed on at that school until you were how old?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
I should be 17 or 18. 17 and then I did one year as a student teacher, before I went to college, in the school where I sat for the scholarship examination, the same school.
 She was, by then the old martinet had left and the next, the senior teacher of the school took the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10705778\charrsid12130839 headship}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
 and she was very nice and very helpful. And then of course I went to college.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Had you always thought of being a teacher?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 No. My mother d
ecided that next to being a mother, being a teacher was the next best job, having care of children and having an influence on their lives.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 So was it her idea more than yours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Yes I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Did you mind this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Yes, I did, to some exte
nt. Because I wanted to learn the violin and I wanted to sing. And I was very fond of home, I was very fond of baking and cooking and I think I should have liked to have stayed at home.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 But you hadn't any option?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 I don't think I had. I was enco
uraged, especially when I, we took the Oxford Senior and I failed in English because I failed in the Literature, and then we had to take the whole syllabus again, so I stayed on another year, to get the English, and then when I failed in English I was rat
her disheartened, as of course a child is, and I was quite prepared to leave it and do something else, but I was encouraged to work hard and get it and keep on and later of course I think I was grateful, for the decision that was made.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Why didn't you just go on as a pupil teacher then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
I think that was just going out, that pupil teacher business. No. The idea then, by the time I had reached the age, the idea was to go to be fully trained, to get the teacher training course, and get the qualification.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Did you have a scholarship or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
No, only the very brilliant girls had a scholarship. No, the fees were not heavy and my parents paid in full. For the college training.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Was there any sort of entrance examination for the college?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
No, we were accepted on the Oxford senior, on the qualifications, that was our examination then, the Oxford senior.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 So you were 18 when you left home for the first time?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 And how did you find it, being away from home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Oh I liked it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 You weren't homesick?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
No, I don't think I was ever homesick. I never have been homesick. I like home, but I have not been homesick. I quite enjoyed it and I think it did me a world of good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 I was just needing that period to gain independence and confidence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 What sort of a place was your college, how big?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
It was only about its second year, it was under the London County Council you know, and that is partly because it was cheap, because it was subsidised. The fees, really my parents couldn't have kept me at home any cheaper. The fees were only }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 \'a3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
25 a year for board, lodging and tuition and laundry I think it was ridiculously cheap, don't you think so? I don't know whether other colleges were so cheap, I don't think they were. And it was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8197580\charrsid12130839 undenominational}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 How big was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Well let me see, oh there'd be probably not more than 300 students, or maybe 350, I'm thinking of the houses, the houses of residence, there'd be about, there were 3 houses with about maybe 60 in each and then we had a lot of day students.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 What sort of backgrounds were these girls from?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Oh like ourselves. Variety. Every kind. Every - every kind of background I should imagine.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 What was it like in a big institution? Were you sharing a room or what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
We had our own, it was quite pleasant really. We had our own study bedrooms. I was in a big house that had been converted of course. And one big room would be split up by walls, partitions, but not to the ceiling, so that we could climb
 up on our beds and look over and waken up our next door neighbour with a few drops of water, if necessary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Were they strict over being in at certain hours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Well it happened to be an awkward time, it was war time, so that they were rather strict
. We got permits on occasions to go out and be later, in later, if we had any, any where to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Could you have visitors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Yes, with permission. There was one small study room where we could entertain visitors to tea. But we didn't have many.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 What sort of holidays did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Well I spent two working holidays when I was in college down in the country, I think it was in, I think it was in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197580\charrsid12130839 Dorset,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
 flax pulling for aeroplane wings. Gangs of us went down there to work on the land. We lived
 in tents. I went on two occasions. We were paid a small nominal sum you know as wages and we were kept, sort of field kitchen affair. And we spent the days flax pulling in gangs. Now its done by machinery I think, it's pulled up, but you see it has to be
 
pulled because there are several inches that are useful grow below the, you know the roots, the stem goes so far, and the longer the stem the better the flax, the better the we've, now it isn't used at all I don't think. But then the holidays were again j
ust at this old, my mother's aunt at Ripon, and that is where my heart has often been, because it is a lovely spot. Most of the Summer holidays were spent at Ripon.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Did being away from home make things rather different when you went back? Did you get on well with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
No, I don't think I did altogether. Because by then I'd acquired a lot of new ideas about people and life generally being away from home and I think I got to be rather argumentative, I went through a period not very happy. 
It wasn't an easy time, because it was the end of the war, we'd lost a lot of boyfriends, people were scattered, people were unhappy, it was a dreadful war, the 1st world war, and I think it affected all of us. And of course we had that explosion you see,
 which affected us, the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197580\charrsid12130839 munitions}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
 works, not far from our house, being blown up. No, life wasn't easy, not for a long period. And then for a time I felt, I felt very lonely, I needed to be loved and to have someone to love, but I was always cautious, of men
's friendship, because of our upbringing I suppose. No confidences with Mother you see and that kind of thing, like there are today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 What were your }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197580\charrsid12130839 parent\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839  attitudes towards your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Well they were always, I will say that all our friends, 
we could take them home. I can't remember taking many }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8197580\charrsid12130839 men friends}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
 home, but most of our girlfriends were always welcomed. In fact, I think at one time we girls were a little bit envious because my mother seemed to mother our girlfriends more than she mothe
red us. They could confide in her more than we could confide in her. She was not easy with us, and other girls seemed to find her easy. Rather funny that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Would your parents always want to know where you were and who you were with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Well I think
 they knew mostly, they knew most of our friends, and if we went out on a Saturday walking, we didn't call it biking then, we called it just going for a walk, we walked miles you see. I think more or less we took it for granted that they knew. And they tr
usted us to behave properly and to come home at a reasonable hour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 They would expect you back at a certain time would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Well if we were, say, later than 10, I think then my mother would begin to be anxious and wonder where we were. That is wh
en we were young you see. Say in our teens. And of course after I had finished, when I was living at home, after I had finished in college, I took it for granted, I think I usually said where I was going and what time I should be back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 When you were still at college would you attend Chapel at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Yes, I did attend a Methodist Church it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Had you any interest in politics at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
I hadn't much, but I had a college friend who was very interested and I think. Through her graduall
y I became more interested. Later on. After I had left college. Because I joined the Liberal Party. Until I found out that they were joining up with the Conservatives and then I left them. They did, they joined up with the Conservatives and then I left th
em, because I didn't like that idea at all.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 Would you still help your mother when you were home on holiday from college?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7802526 C  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2850671  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12086281\charrsid12130839 
Oh yes, I helped all I could, oh yes, I continued to help in the house, and shopping and all that kind of thing.
\par }}